==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saturant
<hw>Sat"u*rant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>saturans</ets>, p. pr. See <er>Saturate</er>.]</ety>
<def>Impregnating to the full; saturating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saturant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Saturant
<hw>Sat"u*rant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
substance used to neutralize or saturate the affinity of another
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An antacid, as magnesia, used to
correct acidity of the stomach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saturate</ent>⟦br⟧
